MAJOR charities have joined forces to offer more support to men affected by prostate cancer. Extra help for prostate sufferers MAJOR charities have joined forces to offer more support to men affected by prostate cancer.Cancer Support Scotland is offering 120 extra appointments at its Glasgow headquarters for patients.The new support service has been made possible by a funding boost from Prostate Cancer UK with the support of The Movember Foundation.Prostate Cancer is the most common cancer in men. 